description: Rosette-forming plant, growing to a maximum of 40cm in height, the small pink orwhite flowershave five petals which grow at the end of the stems. It is common in the spring, and it prefers cool, damp conditions. It first appears in sunlit areas after the first heavy rains. Though, the best stands are found in shaded areas, especially in the uplands, into the early summer. As the days get hotter, the leaves turn a deep red color as they dry out.
location: along the path that leads down to the lower parking lot; Wild Places hike; near stair for climbing wall.
coolFact: The common name miner's lettuce refers to its use by California Gold Rush miners who ate it to get their vitamin C to prevent scurvy.Mild tasting leaves are not unlike spinach in texture
